Traffic & Transit
Power Outage Causing Traffic Delays In Millbrae: Police
Police sent out an alert at 8:57 a.m.
MILLBRAE, CA — Police said they are conducting traffic control Wednesday at an intersection in Millbrae due to a power outage.
At 9:38 a.m. the San Mateo County Sheriff's Office said traffic has been restored and is flowing normally at the intersection of El Camino Real and Victoria Avenue in Millbrae.
Police said power outages are impacting businesses in the 200–400 block of Broadway in Millbrae and are expected to continue for approximately 6–8 hours.
